Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with constructing a formula to axiomatize rectangular grids. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper deals with combinatorial structures such as grids and spectra. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the time and space complexity of recognizing numbers in a set. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of non-deterministic Turing machines and cellular automata. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with grids and their properties.
